00:39:26.100 --> 00:39:31.700
Dalai Lama: I FEEL
VERY HONORED, HUMBLE,
AND DEEPLY MOVED

00:39:31.700 --> 00:39:35.000
THAT YOU SHOULD GIVE
THIS IMPORTANT PRIZE

00:39:35.000 --> 00:39:37.730
TO A SIMPLE BUDDHIST MONK.

00:39:37.730 --> 00:39:41.060
I AM NO ONE SPECIAL.

00:39:41.060 --> 00:39:45.900
I ACCEPT THE PRIZE
WITH PROFOUND GRATITUDE

00:39:45.900 --> 00:39:50.160
ON BEHALF OF THE
OPPRESSED EVERYWHERE

00:39:50.160 --> 00:39:54.160
AND FOR ALL THOSE WHO
STRUGGLE FOR FREEDOM

00:39:54.160 --> 00:39:56.030
AND WORK FOR WORLD PEACE.

00:39:56.030 --> 00:40:00.100
ALL OF US WANT FREEDOM
AND A RIGHT TO DETERMINE

00:40:00.100 --> 00:40:05.430
OUR OWN DESTINY AS
INDIVIDUALS AND AS PEOPLES.

00:40:05.430 --> 00:40:10.600
BECAUSE VIOLENCE CAN ONLY BREED
MORE VIOLENCE AND SUFFERING,

00:40:10.600 --> 00:40:14.860
OUR STRUGGLE MUST
REMAIN NONVIOLENT

00:40:14.860 --> 00:40:17.900
AND FREE OF HATRED.

00:40:17.900 --> 00:40:21.430
WE ARE TRYING TO END THE
SUFFERING OF OUR PEOPLE,

00:40:21.430 --> 00:40:24.730
NOT TO INFLICT
SUFFERING ON OTHERS.

00:40:24.730 --> 00:40:28.860
I PRAY FOR ALL OF US,
OPPRESSOR AND FRIEND,

00:40:28.860 --> 00:40:32.400
THAT TOGETHER WE SUCCEED
IN BUILDING A BETTER WORLD

00:40:32.400 --> 00:40:37.330
THROUGH HUMAN UNDERSTANDING
AND LOVE. THANK YOU.

00:40:37.330 --> 00:40:41.760
[APPLAUSE]

00:40:41.760 --> 00:40:43.760
Thurman: BUDDHA SAID IT.

00:40:43.760 --> 00:40:46.430
HATRED WILL NEVER
PUT AN END TO HATRED,

00:40:46.430 --> 00:40:50.130
AND VIOLENCE WILL NEVER
PUT AN END TO VIOLENCE.

